Summary: A man experiences how messages, conversations, perspective, and truth can change everything in an instant.

Title: A History of Worry
Summary: Set in a symbolic landscape in the guise of Rome, Italy, "A History of Worry" takes viewers on a tour through the psyche of a man whose wife is diagnosed with stage 4 cancer.

Title: Free The Narrative 2
Summary: “Free The Narrative” is a series that tells original and personal stories with some of professional wrestling’s biggest names, and those yet known. “Free The Narrative II” features many more “names” and is the sequel to “Free The Narrative” featuring Matt Cardona vs EC3. After his shocking dismissal from the corporate wrestling realm, join Adam Scherr on a journey of self-discovery in his return to the ring when Scherr battles EC3 in “Free The Narrative II: The Monster In Us All.” What will happen when this “monster” knocks on this “man’s” door?

Title: Seventeen
Summary: Mark, the new student, strives to prevent his best friend's sister Maggie from throwing her life away staying with her bully of a boyfriend instead of going to college, and finds romance in unexpected places.

Title: Aidan Goes England
Summary: Aidan Latham documents a trip to Macclesfield, Britain.

Title: Midnight Run
Summary: After a group of friends exit a Halloween party, two friends, Bryan and Felix, are left behind. During their long walk home, the two soon cross paths between a group of masked skaters, a mysterious driver, and painkillers. All narrated through the sound waves from River City's own, DJ Santiago.

Title: Walking Before Walking
Summary: In “Walking Before Walking,” the filmmaker Adam Amir introduces his son to trees, snow, mist, and sand in the ancient forest of Ch’ich’iyúy Elxwíḵn—and, in so doing, reflects on what he found in himself.

Title: Chakel's Way
Summary: All of our dreams are within reach, but life has a way of happening. For many of us the obstacles that stand in our way will either cause a delay OR it will push us to greatness. MyQueal Lewis of #BlackCreators sets his lens on the journey of, “Chakel’s Way.”

Title: Sam and George
Summary: This is the pilot episode for a Sci-Fi...I mean slice of life show called Sam and George. It's about two roommates named Sam and George. That's basically it. I hope you enjoy!

Title: Those Who Heard and Those Who Saw
Summary: During the Second World War, thousands of Jewish refugees who had fled Nazi oppression were imprisoned in the United Kingdom and sent to work in prison camps in Canada. Using a large archive of never-released audio interviews, Those Who Heard & Those Who Saw tells the story of these prisoners and considers how their experiences connect to those of contemporary refugees.

Title: Vodka: Friend and Foe of the Russians
Summary: What beer is to Germans, vodka is to Russians. The Russians consume around 60 liters of their national drink per capita per year - as cheap liquor, fine drink and home-distilled. But the high alcohol consumption has consequences: every year around 30,000 people in Russia die of alcohol poisoning. WELT reporter Christoph Wanner has taken a closer look at the production and sales of Vodka - a lucrative business in which not everything is right.

Title: Major Coaster Renovation- The Return Of Colossos
Summary: Europe's fastest and highest wooden roller coaster is located in the Heide Park Resort in Soltau. The amusement park has been characterized by the 60 meter high ride since 2001. With a top speed of almost 110 kilometers per hour, “Colossos” was a real crowd puller, with around 20 million guests traveling in 15 years. The restoration began in 2016. New wood, new rails, new technology - the report accompanies the extensive renovation of Germany's most popular wooden roller coaster.

Title: Efflictim
Summary: The loss of a young man's childhood friend causes him to use unhealthy coping mechanisms to deal with his suffering, but he realizes that he must come to terms with his loss and move forward.

Title: The Twerker
Summary: What's a man to do when there's a twerker on the loose?

Title: Everything's Gonna Be Okay
Summary: Two men take a depressing road trip to god knows where.

Title: It's Look Sunshine
Summary: Young-Eun lives with her mother and learns eco-friendly photography. After her mother gets caught in a discarded net submerged in the sea and drowns, Young-Eun moves away.

Title: Planet Earth about to be Recycled
Summary: In March of 1997, 39 members of the Heavens Gate cult committed ritualist suicide. This is their story.

Title: Johann
Summary: A puppet controlled by a disembodied hand creates it's own objects from red material.

Title: Phish 2021-08-01 Ameris Bank Amphitheatre, Alpharetta GA
Summary: Phish 2021-08-01 Ameris Bank Amphitheatre, Alpharetta GA  Webcast  SET 1: Buried Alive > Set Your Soul Free, Reba, My Friend, My Friend, 555, Kill Devil Falls > Gotta Jibboo > Sparkle, Thread, Meat, Run Like an Antelope  SET 2: More > Tweezer > Twist > Piper > Farmhouse > Waste > First Tube  ENCORE: Sleeping Monkey > Tweezer Reprise

Title: Call in the Cheapskates
Summary: Cheapskate Goldy Locks helps a family with out-of-control shopping habits.

Title: Greed
Summary: Two men realize the cost greed has.

Title: CatVideoFest 2021
Summary: CatVideoFest is a compilation reel of the latest and best cat videos culled from countless hours of unique submissions and sourced animations, music videos, and classic internet powerhouses. CatVideoFest is a joyous communal experience, only available in theaters, and raises money for cats in need through partnerships with local cat charities, animal welfare organizations, and shelters to best serve cats in the area.

Title: Deliver Us 1 + 2: Book of Shadows
Summary: Surrealist horror/absurdist comedy Spongebob Squarepants YTP involving doppelgangers, existential torment, and pizza.

Title: Dark Blue Sky
Summary: A short film that only uses photos and intertitles, this visual scenario depicts the sky as the sun sets. Picture yourself as the sunset leads into night.

Title: Budget Hotels: Are They a Con?
Summary: A look at the best and worst hotels Britain has to offer.

Title: Heavy Haulage- In The Jungle
Summary: The São Manoel Hydroelectric Plant: in the heart of Brazil, deep in the Amazon rainforest. Everything the site needs must be transported via a long and arduous route. These transformers weigh over 200 metric tons each - they have to travel 4,000 kilometers before they reach their final destination. The workers at Megatranz are experts: long distances are easy for them. The haulage convoy covers most of the route easily - but the last 100 kilometers are difficult.  The temperature is 40 degrees Celsius in the shade, the conditions merciless, the roads dusty and the bridges old. This is demanding work for the workers and the cargo. But it’s also a bonding experience. Mistakes can be fatal. The way across the river is dangerous. A ferry is repurposed into a barge: a highly risky maneuver. Nerves of steel are just part of the job - but that’s no use when your luck runs out.

Title: Wind Farm Assembly- Off The Coast Of Sylt - Millimeter Work In All Weathers
Summary: Probably the most difficult construction site in Germany is 70 kilometers from Sylt. The sea is up to 32 meters deep and the waves are high even in good weather. A wind park with 80 turbines is being built here under harsh conditions, which will generate climate-friendly electricity for a million people. A mammoth project that is hard to beat in terms of size and complexity. And things are progressing rapidly: specialists erect the almost 150-meter-high wind turbines within a day.

Title: Lost Year
Summary: A reflection of a doomed year.

Title: Chinatown Beat
Summary: Chinatown has had a big hit in 2020 with many business closing down, community members getting harassed and attacked by hate crimes. Yet the community perseveres as the artist continues to work. Henry Chang, born and raised in Chinatown, continues to live and work on Mott street. Part of the self-reclaimed “OG crew” of China- town, he is adored and respected by his community the way community leaders are. While prepping to shoot, Corky Lee, a legendary Asian-American photographer and friend to Henry for over a half a century, died of Covid. Corky's presence and art naturally seeped its way into the film. Henry Chang, the unofficial official community leader of Chinatown walks us through life and art as we transition from the Year of the Rat to the Year of the Ox.

Title: Escape
Summary: A man realizes that his troubles will always come back to him.

Title: Hamilton: The Spaces Performance
Summary: An intepid singer performs all the songs from the hit musical 'Hamilton' as part of a solo and an acapella show on Twitter Spaces

Title: A Quiet Dinner with Friends
Summary: When Marla invites Shelley and her new boyfriend Peter for dinner, her husband John assumes it will be another boring dinner party. He soon discovers there's something odd about Peter. Much to his surprise and confusion no one else notices. As the evening progresses strange things begin to happen, Peter's behavior grows more outrageous, and John finds himself forced to make an impossible choice.

Title: This Is My Story
Summary: Amphibian Stage asked this question of Black men living and working in Fort Worth, Texas, and received deeply personal responses. “This Is My Story” presents three stories from an educator, an event planner and a Veteran Peer Service Coordinator, each of whom has learned to be silent as a means of self-preservation — but at what cost?

Title: Sound of Surf
Summary: “Sound of the Surf” is the historic Rockumentary that tells the TRUE story of Surf Music, before it became an exploited, distorted, Hollywood production. It uses intimate interviews, media archives, personal scrapbooks and home movies to present the stories of the musicians who created the genre. It explores the questions: what is Surf Music, where did it come from, who invented it and what, if anything, did it have to do with SURFING?

Title: Tree Mugger
Summary: A girl prepares for a robbery by practicing on a tree in her backyard.

Title: Buddy Davis' Amazing Adventures: Safari!
Summary: Buddy’s off on his most far-flung adventure yet! From his log cabin in rural Ohio, to the vast savannas of South Africa in search of some of the most amazing creatures God has made. Walk with lions (if you dare!), ride an elephant, and search for other exciting wildlife alongside your favorite adventurer. As you explore the wonders God has made, you’ll enjoy original songs from Buddy, biblical worldview teaching, and Scripture tie-ins.  So fire up the all-terrain vehicle (you’ll need it!), grab your camera, and prepare for another amazing adventure with Buddy Davis!

Title: They Only Have Eyes for You, Spikehunter
Summary: Scrolling through hundreds of pages Insecam.com–over the course of a week I screen recorded thousands of live uploaded still images from footage recorded by cctv camera’s whose owners never changed their password from the default set by the manufacturer. I was thinking about the parallels between the destructive manhandling of nature and the diminishment of human freedom by the vast, overwhelming sea of advertisements we are driven through, leaving undetectable stains on our perception of the world and the necessity for consumption, violence, and ideological ignorance. Hope you feel it.

Title: Riding a Legend
Summary: Enduro rider Didier Goirand rides through one of the most impressive landscapes in Mexico while reliving the legend of the Parícutin volcano.

Title: Stevie Nicks: Live in Concert - The 24 Karat Gold Tour
Summary: The ’24 Karat Gold’ Tour took place between 2016 and 2017 in promotion of Nicks’ eighth solo studio album, released in 2014. Footage from the film was recorded during her shows in Pittsburgh and Indianapolis.

Title: Treacherous Timber: Loggers And Their Mega Tools
Summary: Woodworkers have one of the most dangerous jobs in the world. When ordinary forest companies get stuck, the specialists are called. They remove storm damage in the forest, saw at breathtaking heights and cut down giant rotten trees before the dreaded bark beetle can spread uncontrollably. Whether with the help of a harvester, rope crane or 'flying saw' - you are well equipped for all locations.

Title: Fire in an Empty Room
Summary: Obedient high schooler Henry Roberts has been best friends with Jay Macroni for as long as he can remember. But things are starting to change. With tensions higher than ever, Henry is left with a choice: let flames of his incendiary best friend consume him, or stand up alone for himself.

Title: Hamilton Leithauser - Live at the Knickerbocker Music Center
Summary: Hamilton Leithauser and family play a quarantine set as part of the Knick Live Series.

Title: Aturdir
Summary: The director's true story begins with a child in a situation she has no control over, realizing that this is what the rest of her life looks like. We’re brought in as she’s attending elementary school. One day, her teacher notices bruising on the arm of the child. The child lives in a world of fear and constant edge and someone is finally taking notice of it. This leads to the courageous act of the teacher reaching out to the child’s mother in a request to purchase a new pair of shoes for her student. In the end, through the teacher’s actions, the impact gives the child the inspiration to not give up on her future.

Title: Doobie Run
Summary: Grab your joystick and hit start, because it’s time to play Doobie Run: the video game made for stoners by stoners.

Title: Money, For A Purchase
Summary: In dire need of some cash to buy a panini skillet, a man sets out to find the money he buried all those years ago.

Title: Fast and Furry
Summary: Buckle-up and blast-off with your favorite space heroes, as the mischievous Fuzzlumps Fritz and Blitz - along with many colorful friends and foes alike - fight to save the galaxy from the dreaded Balderdash Bug virus. But, can they do it? It's Fast And Furry, a galactic adventure out of this world.

Title: How Porn is Destroying You and Our Country
Summary: Our young men are suffering from a manufactured addiction to internet pornography, the results of which are invariably swept under the rug. To pursue the truth, you must take control of your desires. As long as they can enslave you to your own desires, they can continue to distort the truth and you will be none the wiser.

Title: Caden Blair: Jokes 4 Myself
Summary: Caden Blair's intimate stand-up 'special' shot with no audience from his bedroom.

Title: Bananza
Summary: A man known only as “The Farmer” lives a quiet life on his farm when one night the farm is ravaged and his wife is kidnapped. The Farmer must give his all to track down the gang and take them out

Title: The Yorkshire Ripper's New Victims
Summary: Documentary telling the story of some of Peter Sutcliffe's other alleged victims male and female claimed to be ignored, marginalised and dismissed by the police.

Title: Masiwei - East Avenue
Summary: Short documentary about Chinese rapper Masiwei.

Title: Cards
Summary: A man battles a mysterious opponent in a game of cards.

Title: The Long Fall
Summary: Bodies and objects chaotically collide in a small house as it plummets down a deep hole. Created using Valve's 2004 Machinima game Garry's Mod during COVID-19 self isolation.

Title: World's Biggest Car Wash- Washing, Waxing, Drying
Summary: Up to 4,000 car washes and around 1,000 interior washes per day; plus a hand wax station, 48 vacuum cleaner spaces, a petrol station and an oil change service: the world's largest car wash in Stuttgart-Feuerbach (Germany) is a superlative system. The documentary takes a look behind the scenes of the family business and shows the enormous logistical effort involved in handling the vehicle masses and the perfect luxury car care.

Title: Deep Sea Fishing- Hard Work On The High Seas
Summary: Deep sea fishing - that's working to the limit. The ships of the German deep sea fishing fleet often stay at sea for months. The hunt for the black halibut takes the team to the Arctic Circle. Storm and snow are part of everyday life here, work on board is dangerous. Great trust in their comrades and their own skills makes the crew a tight-knit community. This documentary accompanies the crew on board one of the largest deep-sea trawlers in the German fleet.

Title: Meet the Numbers 2
Summary: Children will fall in love with these wonderful characters as they "Meet the Numbers." With Meet the Numbers children learned numbers from 0 to 10. Now children can learn numbers from 11 to 20! Preschool Prep Series™ DVDs have won hundreds of awards and are used in millions of homes and schools around the world. You will be amazed at how easily your little one can learn numbers!™

Title: Solar Eclipse
Summary: Two dancers depict the events of a solar eclipse

Title: Charles
Summary: A young couple moves in to their first apartment and encounters a red-headed freckled doll. Soon they discover that their home and doll reveal an evil presence.

Title: Either Side of Midnight
Summary: A lyrical snapshot and celebration of the manic, intoxicating diversity of New York. Four stories collide over one Friday night in Manhattan.

Title: The Sea We've Never Seen
Summary: David’s friend from college comes to visit him in LA, but his flight back to China has been canceled due to the pandemic. During the time they live together, David has a secret that he doesn’t know whether or not he should tell.

Title: Closed for COVID: Hope and Resiliency
Summary: Small Business owners struggling to navigate the economic challenges of a global pandemic find the resiliency to keep their doors open and give back to their communities.

Title: Alice Cooper: Detroit Stories
Summary: 01. Intro

Title: 17. Killer / I Love The Dead Themes
20. Outro
